            <div class="text-sm text-white/50 font-mono uppercase tracking-widest">
              // progsu's comprehensive career development program
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Program Introduction -->
        <div class="mb-16">
          <div class="border border-white/10 bg-white/[0.02] p-8">
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-6" style="font-family: 'Helvetica Neue', sans-serif;">
              What is gitPAID?
            </h2>

            <div class="space-y-6 text-white/70 leading-relaxed" style="font-family: 'Helvetica Neue', sans-serif;">
              <p>
                <strong class="text-white">gitPAID</strong> is progsu's comprehensive career development program designed to take you from coding fundamentals to landing your first tech internship or full-time position. The name represents the journey: mastering <em>git</em> (version control and collaborative development) to getting <em>PAID</em> (landing that dream job).
              </p>

              <p>
                This isn't just another collection of interview prep materials. gitPAID is a structured, battle-tested methodology that breaks down the job search into two critical phases: <strong class="text-blue-400">getting the interview</strong> and <strong class="text-purple-400">passing the interview</strong>. We've distilled the most effective approaches from successful club members who've landed positions at Google, Microsoft, Amazon, and top startups.
              </p>

              <p>
                Most people fail because they focus on the wrong things at the wrong time. Our framework ensures you're building the right skills in the right order, maximizing your chances of success while minimizing wasted effort.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Why This Works -->
        <div class="mb-16">
